{"title": "Leakage of sensitive data in dynamic file generation", "summary": "  It is not uncommon to generate logs, backups, or data exports to static file formats. This rule checks if code exists to write sensitive data to static files. ", "description": "\n\nIt is not uncommon to generate logs, backups, or data exports to static file formats. This rule checks if code exists to write sensitive data to static files.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid code like the following:\n\n```php\n  foreach ($users as $user) {\n    fputcsv($csvFile, [$user['email'], $user['address']]);\n  }\n```\n\nIn instances where writing sensitive data is intentional, make sure to document its location according to your internal policies.\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-313"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_file_generation"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}